  const errors = validationResult(req);
  if (!errors.isEmpty()) return res.status(400).json({ errors: errors.array() });
  // ... handle request
});
```

### 6. 🌐 Don't Hardcode the Port
```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));
```
This avoids accidental exposure and makes the app portable across environments.

### 7. 🔒 Restrict CORS (if applicable)
```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({ origin: 'https://yourdomain.com' })); // Avoid wildcard '*' in production
```

### 8. 📝 Avoid Leaking Sensitive Data
The `/users` route currently returns email addresses. Consider:
- Only returning data the requester is authorized to see (add authentication middleware)
- Omitting sensitive fields from public endpoints

---

